content:
 Art. 4.129. 
Data controller
 The Royal Federation of Belgian Notaries, hereinafter referred to as "the administrator", is responsible for managing and organising the central register of successions.
 The manager is considered, as far as the central register of successions is concerned, to be the controller, within the meaning of Article 4, 7), of Regulation (EU) 2016/679 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 27 April 2016 on the protection of individuals with      regard to the processing of personal data and on the free movement of such data, and repealing Directive 95/46/EC.
 The data controller shall appoint a data protection officer. The Data Protection Officer is more specifically responsible for
  1¡ providing qualified advice on the protection of privacy, the security of personal data and information and the processing thereof;
  2¡ informing and advising managers processing personal data of their obligations under this law and the general framework for data protection and privacy;
  3¡ establishing, implementing, updating and monitoring a security and privacy protection policy;
  4¡ to be the contact point for the Data Protection Authority;
  5¡ carrying out other tasks relating to the protection of privacy and security that are determined by the King, after obtaining the opinion of the Data Protection Authority.
  In carrying out his duties, the Data Protection Officer acts independently and reports directly to the manager.
  The King may, after obtaining the opinion of the Data Protection Authority, determine the rules on the basis of which the Data Protection Officer carries out his duties.
